This paper focuses on natural language processing (NLP) tasks in the medical domain, specifically radiological text classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related tasks. The paper also discusses the use of transfer learning techniques and transformer-based models, which are common in machine learning and deep learning research, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with image-based medical data (CT scans), which could place it in the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of pretraining and deep learning models to achieve state-of-the-art results, which could place it in the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category, which deals with techniques for retrieving relevant information from large datasets.
